Ghana to Spend $1.8 Billion of China Loans in West, GNA Says

-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 
2011-08-25T10:59:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/ghana-to-spend-1-8-billion-of-china-loans-in-west-gna-says.html
Ghana  will spend $1.8 billion of a
total $3 billion in lending from the  China Development Bank  on
infrastructure projects in the Western region, the Ghana News
Agency reported, citing Emmanuel Armah-Kofi Buah, deputy
minister for energy.  The money will be used to build infrastructure for a
natural gas project, a petroleum terminal and road and railway
routes, the Accra-based news agency cited Buah as saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 